                <head>No. 262<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On September 6, the Embassy in Belgrade was informed by the Yugoslav Government
                    that Soviet-Yugoslav trade talks would begin that week in Belgrade, with the
                    Yugoslav Government primarily interested in obtaining Soviet wheat. This
                    information was transmitted to the Department of State in telegram 188 from
                    Belgrade, September 6. (661.6831/9–654)</p>
            </div>
